<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 58.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-01"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 1, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatch of the 5th of January last, and to thank you,
                            in the President’s name, for the generous sentiments which you have
                            expressed in regard to his policy and his health.</p>
                        <p>The experiment of reconstruction is begun in Louisiana, Arkansas, and
                            Tennessee under what seem to be favorable auspices. The legislature of
                            Maryland has provided for taking the sense of the people of that State
                            upon the question of emancipation.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>